children.subject:
I was able to get CS 70 to count for the Math 55 requirement for my math major, but usually it doesn’t work the other way around, since CS 70 covers probability & Math 55 doesn’t. Similarly, since EE 16A and EE 16B cover circuits along with linear algebra, I don’t think Math 54 alone will replace the EE 16A requirement — in the past, Math 54 + EE 16B or Math 54 + EE 16A would fulfill the requirement but it might not anymore. 

In any case, I’d highly recommend emailing a CS advisor, or going to drop in advising on Wednesday — they’d know the answers to these questions better than anyone here!! :)

history.content: I am a junior transfer student from UCI, this is the first semester I am at Cal. I have just declared the math major. I want to double major computer science. I wonder if I use Math 55 to exchange CS70 and Math 54 to exchange EE16A.
history.subject: Some questions of the course equivalency of double major
